{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"So, a funny thing happened"},{"time":3000,"text":"on my way to becoming a brilliant,\nworld-class neuropsychologist:"},{"time":8079,"text":"I had a baby."},{"time":10005,"text":"And that's not to say"},{"time":11284,"text":"I ever went on to become a brilliant,\nworld-class neuropsychologist."},{"time":15246,"text":"Sorry, TED."},{"time":17715,"text":"But I did go on to be a reasonably astute,"},{"time":21398,"text":"arguably world-class worrier."},{"time":24532,"text":"One of my girlfriends\nin graduate school, Marie,"},{"time":27100,"text":"said, \"Kim, I figured it out."},{"time":29869,"text":"It's not that you're more neurotic\nthan everyone else;"},{"time":32700,"text":"it's just that you're more honest\nabout how neurotic you are.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":36221,"text":"So in the spirit of full disclosure,"},{"time":39259,"text":"I brought some pictures to share."},{"time":41892,"text":"Awwww."}]},{"cues":[{"time":43124,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":44149,"text":"I'll just say: July."}]},{"cues":[{"time":46700,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":51700,"text":"Zip!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":53139,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":54164,"text":"For safety."}]},{"cues":[{"time":55489,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":57176,"text":"Water wings --"},{"time":59092,"text":"an inch of water."},{"time":62469,"text":"And then, finally, all suited up"},{"time":64487,"text":"for the 90-minute drive\nto Copper Mountain."},{"time":67279,"text":"So you can get kind of a feel for this."},{"time":71255,"text":"So my baby, Vander,\nis eight years old now."},{"time":74723,"text":"And, despite being cursed\nwith my athletic inability,"},{"time":79364,"text":"he plays soccer."},{"time":80961,"text":"He's interested in playing football."},{"time":82962,"text":"He wants to learn how to ride a unicycle."}]},{"cues":[{"time":85247,"text":"So why would I worry?"},{"time":87470,"text":"Because this is what I do.\nThis is what I teach."},{"time":90471,"text":"It's what I study. It's what I treat."},{"time":92567,"text":"And I know that kids\nget concussed every year."},{"time":96683,"text":"In fact, more than four million people\nsustain a concussion every year,"},{"time":100105,"text":"and these data are just\namong kids under 14"},{"time":102700,"text":"who were seen in emergency rooms."},{"time":104986,"text":"And so when kids sustain a concussion,"},{"time":107700,"text":"we talk about them getting dinged\nor getting their bell rung,"},{"time":110700,"text":"but what is it that\nwe're really talking about?"},{"time":113400,"text":"Let's take a look."}]},{"cues":[{"time":115854,"text":"[Concussive Force]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":119053,"text":"\"Starsky and Hutch\"? Arguably, yes."},{"time":122622,"text":"So, a car accident."},{"time":123906,"text":"Forty miles an hour into a fixed barrier:"},{"time":126208,"text":"35 Gs."},{"time":131368,"text":"A heavyweight boxer punches\nyou straight in the face:"},{"time":134417,"text":"58 Gs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":137535,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":142467,"text":"In case you missed it, we'll look again."},{"time":144887,"text":"So look to the right-hand\nside of the screen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":148751,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":153397,"text":"What would you say?"},{"time":155604,"text":"How many Gs?"},{"time":159081,"text":"Close."},{"time":160891,"text":"Seventy-two?"},{"time":162700,"text":"Would it be crazy to know:"},{"time":164926,"text":"103 Gs?"},{"time":167628,"text":"The average concussive impact"},{"time":169394,"text":"is 95 Gs."},{"time":172700,"text":"Now, when the kid\non the right doesn't get up,"},{"time":176067,"text":"we know they've had a concussion."}]},{"cues":[{"time":177700,"text":"But how about the kid on the left,"},{"time":179349,"text":"or the athlete that leaves\nthe field of play?"},{"time":181867,"text":"How do we know if he or she\nhas sustained a concussion?"},{"time":186342,"text":"How do we know"},{"time":187695,"text":"that legislation that would require\nthey be pulled from play,"},{"time":191279,"text":"cleared for return to play,"},{"time":193382,"text":"applies to them?"},{"time":195485,"text":"The definition of concussion"},{"time":197051,"text":"doesn't actually require\na loss of consciousness."},{"time":199708,"text":"It requires only a change\nin consciousness,"},{"time":202485,"text":"and that can be any one\nor a number of symptoms,"},{"time":205121,"text":"including feeling foggy, feeling dizzy,"},{"time":208303,"text":"hearing a ringing in your ear,"},{"time":210002,"text":"being more impulsive\nor hostile than usual."}]},{"cues":[{"time":213509,"text":"So given all of that and given\nhow darn neurotic I am,"},{"time":216811,"text":"how do I get any sleep at all?"},{"time":219392,"text":"Because I know our brains are resilient."},{"time":224069,"text":"They're designed to recover\nfrom an injury."},{"time":228450,"text":"If -- God forbid --"},{"time":230700,"text":"any of us left here tonight\nand sustained a concussion,"},{"time":233920,"text":"most of us would go on to fully recover\ninside of a couple hours"},{"time":237420,"text":"to a couple of weeks."},{"time":238890,"text":"But kids are more vulnerable\nto brain injury."},{"time":241235,"text":"In fact, high-school athletes\nare three times more likely"},{"time":244544,"text":"to sustain catastrophic injuries"},{"time":246916,"text":"relative even to their college-age peers,"},{"time":249441,"text":"and it takes them longer\nto return to a symptom-free baseline."},{"time":254748,"text":"After that first injury,"},{"time":257002,"text":"their risk for second injury\nis exponentially greater."},{"time":260832,"text":"From there, their risk for a third injury,\ngreater still, and so on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":266752,"text":"And here's the really alarming part:"},{"time":270143,"text":"We don't fully understand\nthe long-term impact of multiple injuries."},{"time":275899,"text":"You guys may be familiar\nwith this research"},{"time":278047,"text":"that's coming out of the NFL."},{"time":280490,"text":"In a nutshell,\nthis research suggests that,"},{"time":283231,"text":"among retired NFL players\nwith three or more career concussions,"},{"time":288498,"text":"the incidence of early-onset\ndementing disease"},{"time":291498,"text":"is much greater than it\nis for the general population."},{"time":294826,"text":"So you've all seen that --\nNew York Times, you've seen it."},{"time":297700,"text":"What you may not be familiar with"},{"time":299326,"text":"is that this research was spearheaded\nby NFL wives who said,"},{"time":304469,"text":"\"Isn't it weird\nthat my 46-year-old husband"},{"time":307470,"text":"is forever losing his keys?\""},{"time":309533,"text":"\"Isn't it weird that\nmy 47-year-old husband"},{"time":312328,"text":"is forever losing the car?\""},{"time":314835,"text":"\"Isn't it weird that\nmy 48-year-old husband"},{"time":317724,"text":"is forever losing his way home"},{"time":319769,"text":"in the car, from the driveway?\""},{"time":323038,"text":"I may have forgotten to mention\nthat my son is an only child."},{"time":328860,"text":"So it's going to be really important"},{"time":331664,"text":"that he be able to drive\nme around someday."}]},{"cues":[{"time":336016,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":337190,"text":"So, how do we guarantee\nthe safety of our kids?"},{"time":342549,"text":"How can we 100 percent\nguarantee the safety of our kids?"},{"time":347406,"text":"Let me tell you what I've come up with."}]},{"cues":[{"time":350883,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":355700,"text":"If only."},{"time":357032,"text":"My little boy's right there,\nand he's like, \"She's not kidding."},{"time":360045,"text":"She's totally not kidding.\""},{"time":362214,"text":"So in all seriousness:"},{"time":364806,"text":"Should my kid play football?"},{"time":366477,"text":"Should your kid play football?"},{"time":368288,"text":"I don't know."},{"time":369478,"text":"But I do know there are\nthree things you can do."},{"time":373009,"text":"The first: study up."},{"time":375875,"text":"You have to be familiar with the issues\nwe're talking about today."},{"time":379628,"text":"There are some great resources out there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":382218,"text":"The CDC has a program, HEADS UP."},{"time":384536,"text":"It's at CDC.gov."},{"time":386194,"text":"HEADS UP is specific\nto concussion in kids."},{"time":389606,"text":"The second is a resource\nI'm personally really proud of."},{"time":392880,"text":"We've just rolled this out\nin the last couple months --"},{"time":395546,"text":"CO Kids With Brain Injury."},{"time":397239,"text":"This is a great resource\nfor student athletes,"},{"time":399915,"text":"teachers, parents, professionals,\nathletic and coaching staff."},{"time":404328,"text":"It's a great place to start\nif you have questions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":408883,"text":"The second thing is: speak up."},{"time":412205,"text":"Just two weeks ago,"},{"time":413438,"text":"a bill introduced by Senator Kefalas"},{"time":415439,"text":"that would have required\nathletes, kids under 18,"},{"time":419373,"text":"to wear a helmet\nwhen they're riding their bike,"},{"time":421711,"text":"died in committee."},{"time":424422,"text":"It died, in large part,"},{"time":426203,"text":"because it lacked constituent buy-in;"},{"time":429157,"text":"it lacked stakeholder traction."},{"time":431660,"text":"Now, I'm not here to tell you"},{"time":433100,"text":"what kind of legislation\nyou should or shouldn't support,"},{"time":436025,"text":"but I am going to tell you\nthat, if it matters to you,"},{"time":439123,"text":"your legislators need to know that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":442644,"text":"Speak up also with coaching staff."},{"time":444491,"text":"Ask about what kind\nof protective equipment is available."},{"time":447492,"text":"What's the budget\nfor protective equipment?"},{"time":449565,"text":"How old it is?"},{"time":451139,"text":"Maybe offer to spearhead\na fundraiser to buy new gear."}]},{"cues":[{"time":454869,"text":"Which brings us to: suit up."},{"time":457890,"text":"Wear a helmet."},{"time":460422,"text":"The only way to prevent a bad outcome"},{"time":463700,"text":"is to prevent that first injury\nfrom happening."},{"time":467700,"text":"Recently, one of my graduate\nstudents, Tom, said,"},{"time":472283,"text":"\"Kim, I've decided to wear a bike helmet\non the way to class.\""},{"time":476684,"text":"And Tom knows that that little bit\nof foam in a bike helmet"},{"time":480604,"text":"can reduce the g-force of impact by half."},{"time":484658,"text":"Now, I thought it was because I have\nthis totally compelling helmet crusade,"},{"time":489643,"text":"this epiphany of Tom's."},{"time":491786,"text":"As it turns out, it occurred\nto Tom that a $20 helmet"},{"time":495477,"text":"is a good way to protect\na $100,000 graduate education."}]},{"cues":[{"time":499700,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":501748,"text":"So ..."},{"time":505079,"text":"Should Vander play football?"},{"time":508111,"text":"I can't say no,"},{"time":509438,"text":"but I can guarantee that every time\nhe leaves the house,"},{"time":513700,"text":"that kid's wearing a helmet --"},{"time":516422,"text":"like, to the car,"},{"time":518423,"text":"or at school."},{"time":521088,"text":"So whether athlete, scholar,"},{"time":523793,"text":"overprotected kid, neurotic mom,"},{"time":526492,"text":"or otherwise,"},{"time":528302,"text":"here's my baby, Vander,"},{"time":530214,"text":"reminding you"},{"time":531619,"text":"to mind your matter."}]},{"cues":[{"time":534700,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":535892,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}